Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.32,0:01:39.47,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,The one who attacked Ishida…
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.46,0:01:41.45,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,…was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.75,0:01:45.99,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.67,0:01:47.92,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What’s got you so freaked?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.45,0:01:50.63,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Something’s happening to Inoue!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.31,0:01:54.46,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Relax.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.28,0:01:57.72,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I have no intention of \Ndoing anything to you yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.69,0:02:06.60,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,For today, I’ll head on home right \Nafter I punish this disobedient boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.25,0:02:12.40,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.40,0:02:16.16,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,You’re as kind-hearted \Nas I had heard you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.66,0:02:19.74,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,You can’t bear seeing \Neven an enemy get hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.46,0:02:22.25,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,That’s not what this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.98,0:02:25.54,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,If you’re the one who attacked Ishida,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.25,0:02:28.37,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t allow you to get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.34,0:02:32.68,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I see…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.80,0:02:45.58,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Who’re you calling?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.58,0:02:47.27,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Inoue, who else?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.48,0:02:51.52,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Better not.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.55,0:02:55.02,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,That moment when she’s distracted by the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.02,0:02:56.78,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,ringtone might give the enemy an opening.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.35,0:02:59.23,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,It’s that bad…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.54,0:03:00.65,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t know…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.49,0:03:04.07,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,But her Spiritual Pressure \Nis under tremendous strain…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.25,0:03:10.10,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Is this the right direction?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.10,0:03:11.45,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.45,0:03:12.92,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,But I can’t pin down the location
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.92,0:03:15.25,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,with my Spiritual Pressure perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.30,0:03:20.30,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,If you’ve got the direction right, \NI think I know where she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.24,0:03:22.51,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,If we keep going…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.05,0:03:24.65,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,we’ll reach Inoue’s place!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.57,0:03:40.17,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,If I’m the one who attacked Ishida,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.58,0:03:43.49,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,you can’t allow me to get away…eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.83,0:03:49.49,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Such an ordinary line.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.76,0:03:51.16,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,It’s not very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.49,0:03:55.04,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,It’ll never make it into any book.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.26,0:04:00.84,B2,SHISHIGAWARA,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.08,0:04:02.84,B2,SHISHIGAWARA,0000,0000,0000,,What’s the matter with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.84,0:04:04.55,B2,SHISHIGAWARA,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Tsukishima is serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.12,0:04:07.08,B2,SHISHIGAWARA,0000,0000,0000,,He’s super scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.08,0:04:10.45,B2,SHISHIGAWARA,0000,0000,0000,,You won’t get off with just a beating!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.87,0:04:12.22,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Please be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.60,0:04:16.36,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I’m not doing this for your sake…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.28,0:04:18.48,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Sushigawara.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.98,0:04:24.20,B2,SHISHIGAWARA (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It’s Shishigawara…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.42,0:04:27.99,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have to focus…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.58,0:04:30.93,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No telling what his next move will be.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.87,0:04:34.95,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He’s already taken out his sword,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.95,0:04:37.79,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}so maybe I should put up Santenkesshun…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.72,0:04:42.03,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But that might look like I’m \Nprovoking him to attack.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.85,0:04:46.76,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is there some other way to stop him?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.35,0:04:57.75,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,St…Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.19,0:04:59.57,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Santenkesshun!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.53,0:05:15.62,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Where’s Inoue’s unit?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.62,0:05:16.83,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,403!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.83,0:05:17.58,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.89,0:05:30.97,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Inoue!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.66,0:05:33.43,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay, Inoue?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.65,0:05:38.85,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Inoue!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.66,0:05:47.82,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I’m not cut?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.31,0:05:54.48,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That can’t be…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.89,0:05:59.55,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I definitely felt the blade \Ncutting deeply into my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.84,0:06:03.74,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Inoue!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.46,0:06:08.01,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Kurosaki?! Sado!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.58,0:06:10.08,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you guys here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.58,0:06:11.78,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.08,0:06:16.73,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Chad said something was wrong \Nwith your Spiritual Pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.34,0:06:18.52,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.04,0:06:21.54,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Those fluctuations in your Spiritual \NPressure weren’t normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.93,0:06:23.98,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly happened, Inoue?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.43,0:06:25.67,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.67,0:06:27.15,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,R-Really?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.32,0:06:31.41,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing happened, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.03,0:06:34.86,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I was bent over in pain \Nbecause of a stomach ache—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.86,0:06:35.95,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,maybe that was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.95,0:06:37.40,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,That couldn’t be…
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.81,0:06:40.58,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn’t there another Spiritual \NPressure here until a minute ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.28,0:06:42.58,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Who was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.96,0:06:45.56,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Who? My friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.56,0:06:48.76,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I met my friend here and...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.54,0:06:51.90,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A friend?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.54,0:06:57.78,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That was Tsukishima.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.94,0:07:04.55,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,After my friend left, my \Nstomach began to hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.14,0:07:06.48,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,That’s all it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.56,0:07:08.80,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A friend?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.10,0:07:15.73,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Was Tsukishima my friend?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.58,0:07:19.62,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about making you two worry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.55,0:07:21.25,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.08,0:07:25.29,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He’s the one who attacked Ishida.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.15,0:07:32.51,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll be sure to tell \Nyou if anything happens!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.18,0:07:36.60,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,So let me know if anything \Nhappens to either of you, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.60,0:07:38.33,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sure…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.82,0:07:46.00,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can’t tell Kurosaki.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.64,0:07:49.51,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Well…we’ll be going, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.51,0:07:51.95,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! See you tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.60,0:07:58.03,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That was strange…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.58,0:08:02.97,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why did I think he was \Nmy friend for a moment?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.07,0:08:08.02,B2,ORIHIME (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What in me did he cut?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.41,0:08:17.32,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.73,0:08:19.06,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think happened to Inoue?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.08,0:08:21.06,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.86,0:08:27.34,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,I’m not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.77,0:08:32.80,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Inoue doesn’t know that Ichigo’s \Ngetting his powers back.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.53,0:08:37.45,B2,CHAD (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She doesn’t want to drag Ichigo \Ninto a fight because of her.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.17,0:08:39.57,B2,CHAD (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She wants to keep the danger{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.57,0:08:42.03,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}she’s in away from Ichigo more than anyone.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.39,0:08:46.94,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,She said nothing was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.41,0:08:49.88,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,I guess we have to take her word.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.86,0:08:54.43,B2,CHAD (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I agree with her that it’s too risky {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.43,0:08:57.72,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}to involve Ichigo in a fight \Nin his present condition.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.84,0:09:03.54,B2,CHAD (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I’ll get in touch with Inoue again later.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.49,0:09:08.75,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,I’m sure it must’ve been an error \Nin my Spiritual Pressure perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.33,0:09:10.61,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.53,0:09:16.81,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.76,0:09:31.88,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.88,0:09:33.01,B2,KUTSUZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.90,0:09:36.13,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.23,0:09:39.17,B2,KUTSUZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You’ve had enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.17,0:09:40.74,B2,KUTSUZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,You should be ashamed of yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.74,0:09:41.97,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,What’re you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.21,0:09:47.73,B2,KUTSUZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,I realize you’re happy that all’s \Ngoing well with Ichigo, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.01,0:09:50.93,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,It’s not like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.42,0:09:54.89,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Riruka!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.89,0:09:57.99,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Why don’t you also go home already?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.45,0:10:00.39,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.98,0:10:03.24,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t ignore me, damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.32,0:10:12.32,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah, it’s empty!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.32,0:10:14.49,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Kutsuzawa, give me another!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.50,0:10:16.67,B2,KUTSUZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.94,0:10:18.32,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.32,0:10:21.03,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,What’s one more?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.39,0:10:22.64,B2,KUTSUZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.53,0:10:28.09,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, don’t be like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.09,0:10:29.44,B2,KUTSUZAWA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.01,0:10:31.05,B2,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,Kugo…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.05,0:10:32.61,B2,YUKIO,0000,0000,0000,,It’s your direct line.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.58,0:10:42.76,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.93,0:10:49.16,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,All right. I’ll open it right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.26,0:11:06.45,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Inoue and Chad won’t say anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.03,0:11:09.39,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,but something definitely happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.82,0:11:18.40,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,It was probably the same \Nguy who attacked Ishida.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.17,0:11:21.23,B2,JACKIE,0000,0000,0000,,Kugo…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.23,0:11:22.11,B2,JACKIE,0000,0000,0000,,You think it’s?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.26,0:11:24.28,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.06,0:11:27.05,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,It was probably Tsukishima’s doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.05,0:11:28.95,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,So you do know him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.22,0:11:35.42,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukishima is a Fullbringer, like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.92,0:11:38.13,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,And…
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.86,0:11:41.97,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,he was once one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.00,0:11:55.29,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,UNAGIYA
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.28,0:11:51.49,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.84,0:11:55.53,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.85,0:12:00.60,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,That hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.60,0:12:03.06,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,This door opens toward the stairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.06,0:12:05.54,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I warned you before to \Nbe careful when opening it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.54,0:12:07.03,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,-How many years have you been living here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.08,0:12:07.03,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,-Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.27,0:12:09.37,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Where have you been?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.37,0:12:12.16,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Taking days off again without telling me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.70,0:12:15.79,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, come on in!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.22,0:12:18.01,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll hear your excuse inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.89,0:12:21.47,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,No, here is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.87,0:12:25.22,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.62,0:12:28.43,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.07,0:12:30.99,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You want some time off?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.99,0:12:32.39,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you crazy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.88,0:12:35.85,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,You’ve been taking off this entire time!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.32,0:12:39.49,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Just how much work are you \Nplanning on skipping?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.49,0:12:41.10,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you listening?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.73,0:12:44.00,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I’m sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.69,0:12:48.24,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that’s all I wanted to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.53,0:12:50.24,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Wait…just a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.24,0:12:50.91,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.73,0:12:56.83,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t know what’s going on with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.67,0:12:59.97,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,but stop worrying about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.91,0:13:03.53,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I’m not one of your classmates!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.53,0:13:04.84,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I’m a grown-up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.51,0:13:10.47,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,I’m too old to have a kid \Nlike you worrying about me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.26,0:13:14.44,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,That’s why, if something \Nhappened, spit it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.35,0:13:19.32,B2,IKUMI,0000,0000,0000,,It’s okay for kids to rely on adults.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.72,0:13:28.24,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Ms. Ikumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.74,0:13:51.22,B2,GINJO (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tsukishima {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.95,0:13:55.23,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}used to be our leader.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.36,0:14:00.85,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We came together for a shared purpose{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.85,0:14:03.89,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and worked together to erase our powers.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.30,0:14:08.06,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tsukishima discovered a way {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.06,0:14:12.20,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}to transfer our powers to \Na Substitute Soul Reaper.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.20,0:14:13.87,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He was our leader.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.83,0:14:15.54,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.35,0:14:18.78,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}after the Substitute Soul \NReaper we finally found{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.78,0:14:22.21,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}accepted the powers of several \Nof our group members,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.84,0:14:26.53,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tsukishima suddenly had a change of heart.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.72,0:14:34.58,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He killed both the Substitute Soul Reaper{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.58,0:14:37.69,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and the members of our group \Nwho gave him their powers,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.77,0:14:42.29,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and disappeared from our ranks.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.29,0:14:46.15,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Or…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.15,0:14:51.55,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}perhaps that was his objective all along.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.40,0:14:55.41,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\b0}Let me show you something.{\b1}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.50,0:15:11.09,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This was the Substitute Soul \NReaper’s Combat Pass.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.26,0:15:14.40,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don’t know what Tsukishima’s \Ntrue intentions are.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.14,0:15:18.41,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He wasn’t the kind of guy \Nwho’d tell you his secrets.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.41,0:15:21.62,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and he hasn’t shown himself \Nto us since that day.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.70,0:15:25.07,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That’s why, right now, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.07,0:15:28.16,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}there’s only one thing I \Ndo know about Tsukishima.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.74,0:15:31.47,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}His aim is to prevent us{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.47,0:15:34.70,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}from making contact with you, \Na Substitute Soul Reaper.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.22,0:15:40.41,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}His actions support that theory.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.73,0:15:43.42,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He attacked Uryu Ishida,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.59,0:15:46.92,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}made contact with Orihime Inoue,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.77,0:15:49.45,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and tried to attract your attention{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.06,0:15:55.38,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}using a different, and more \Nviolent, means than we did.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.32,0:16:01.21,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ginjo…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.49,0:16:03.56,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.46,0:16:08.70,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I know what you’re thinking.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.70,0:16:09.69,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But don’t rush.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.38,0:16:13.30,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now that Tsukishima’s \Nmade his next move… {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.30,0:16:14.91,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}we want to speed things up too.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.58,0:16:18.29,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We’ll start preparing for your \Nnext training session right away.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.79,0:16:20.87,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We’ll contact you when we’re ready.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.39,0:16:26.21,B2,GINJO,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So for now, go on home tonight.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.78,0:16:47.61,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dad…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.25,0:16:58.45,B2,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,What’s the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.04,0:17:09.21,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,No, it’s nothing…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.73,0:17:13.05,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s go someplace else.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.97,0:17:15.43,B2,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.85,0:17:18.47,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.57,0:17:25.85,B2,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.59,0:17:27.86,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Let’s do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.73,0:17:38.98,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I forgot…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.71,0:17:40.48,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.99,0:17:43.55,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So many things happened all at once{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.55,0:17:45.91,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}that I tried to erase it from my mind…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.51,0:17:49.34,B2,GINJO (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Just how much do you know about {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.34,0:17:52.50,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Urahara that makes you \Nthink you understand him?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.81,0:17:56.11,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Should I chase after him \Nand ask him right now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.92,0:18:02.00,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No…what if Urahara is really my enemy?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.60,0:18:06.02,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Could I do anything against him now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.09,0:18:09.17,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This isn’t good…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.53,0:18:13.12,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i0}I've got to regain my powers \Nas soon as possible…!{\i1}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.41,0:18:28.90,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.90,0:18:30.46,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah…{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.82,0:18:32.41,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I’m fine, I’m fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.41,0:18:33.67,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.02,0:18:36.88,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,My kitchen came tumbling down…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.45,0:18:38.85,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,I see…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.81,0:18:42.39,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,So, it’s true?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.72,0:18:44.68,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.34,0:18:53.39,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I’m positive I was cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.04,0:18:57.28,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,But when I came to, there was no wound,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.67,0:19:00.97,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,and the people who came here were gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.89,0:19:08.24,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,And then, when you and Kurosaki came…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.89,0:19:12.46,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,for a split second, I thought of that person
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.98,0:19:16.21,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,as a “friend.”
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.64,0:19:19.38,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.85,0:19:21.33,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.33,0:19:24.38,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t really understand \Nwhat I’m saying either.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.38,0:19:28.23,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I just felt like he was my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.08,0:19:32.96,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It’s not like I mistook \Nhim for someone else {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.96,0:19:34.32,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}or that I was mistaken.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.82,0:19:36.74,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,How should I put it…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.32,0:19:39.82,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,It felt like I thought about the past and…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.43,0:19:44.50,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}suddenly I remembered who he was.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.07,0:19:48.75,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, Sado.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.21,0:19:54.62,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}His abilities seem terribly frightening.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.62,0:19:55.69,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.69,0:19:57.21,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.56,0:20:00.26,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,You said there were two of them together?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.63,0:20:01.50,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Huh?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.50,0:20:02.39,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yes.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.39,0:20:05.01,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember their names?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.01,0:20:06.14,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.14,0:20:08.10,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was Tsukishima…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.94,0:20:10.31,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and Sushigawara.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.16,0:20:21.32,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,May I continue, Shishigawara?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.99,0:20:24.24,B2,SHISHIGAWARA,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.96,0:20:26.33,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Listen…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.82,0:20:29.13,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,As far as this matter is concerned,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.13,0:20:30.70,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,you don’t need to do anything further.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.20,0:20:33.96,B2,SHISHIGAWARA,0000,0000,0000,,But! As your apprentice, I…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.63,0:20:38.13,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Will you stop with that apprentice thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.13,0:20:39.80,B2,SHISHIGAWARA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! I’m sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.93,0:20:43.05,B2,SHISHIGAWARA,0000,0000,0000,,As your apprentice!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.05,0:20:49.01,B2,SHISHIGAWARA,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t think it’s right to just \Nwatch quietly as you do your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.96,0:20:57.19,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,By “this matter,” I meant Orihime Inoue.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.59,0:21:02.54,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I’ve already placed it inside her.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.89,0:21:08.08,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,No further contact is necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.06,0:21:12.87,B2,SHISHIGAWARA,0000,0000,0000,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.51,0:21:18.79,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Who should I go next?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.90,0:21:32.91,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Yasutora Sado?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.92,0:21:35.79,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,Or Ichigo Kurosaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.68,0:21:42.65,B2,TSUKISHIMA,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what Ginjo would say
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.16,0:21:46.87,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,if I went after Ichigo Kurosaki directly?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.37,0:23:22.73,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,So Sado, about Sushigawara…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.73,0:23:25.38,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, tell me about this Sushigawara guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.42,0:23:27.33,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.33,0:23:31.06,B2,ORIHIME,0000,0000,0000,,Talking about Sushigawara is making \Nme want to eat some sushi…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.06,0:23:31.97,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.97,0:23:33.23,B2,CHAD,0000,0000,0000,,Me too!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.14,0:23:36.66,B2,KON,0000,0000,0000,,Illustrated Guide to Soul Reapers!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.43,0:23:39.03,B2,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,If we’re going someplace else,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.03,0:23:41.56,B2,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,there’s a place that I’m fond of.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.56,0:23:42.77,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,That you’re fond of?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.06,0:23:44.18,B2,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.18,0:23:45.56,B2,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,With lots of cute ones…
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.56,0:23:48.11,B2,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,You can touch all you want!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.09,0:23:49.13,OS,CAPTION,0000,0000,0000,,PLACE FOR GROWNUPS
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.11,0:23:49.32,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,No no no no!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.66,0:23:52.15,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,I have my beloved Masaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.15,0:23:53.54,B2,ISSHIIN,0000,0000,0000,,-I gave her my word that I wouldn’t go
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.53,0:23:53.97,B2,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,-Come on, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.54,0:23:54.83,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,-to hostess bars and places like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.97,0:23:54.83,B2,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,-Let’s go!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.11,0:23:58.04,B2,FEMALE CLERK,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.04,0:23:59.40,B2,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Upsy-daisy!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.14,0:24:02.01,B2,URAHARA,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, let’s talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.01,0:24:03.22,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,A cat café…?